  "prompt": "What does Obama's mother-in-law do all day in the White House?",
  "response": "Barack Obama's mother-in-law is Marian Robinson, the mother of Michelle Obama. During Barack Obama's presidency from 2009 to 2017, Marian Robinson did not reside in the White House on a permanent basis. Instead, her role was primarily that of a supportive family member.\n\nWhen Marian Robinson visited the White House, her activities typically included:\n\n1. **Family Support:** Spending time with the First Family, offering emotional support, and participating in family gatherings.\n2. **Public Engagements:** Occasionally accompanying Michelle Obama to public events or official functions when appropriate.\n3. **Private Activities:** Engaging in personal interests, hobbies, and spending quality time away from official duties.\n\nIt's important to note that Marian Robinson did not hold an official position or have specific responsibilities within the White House administration. Her presence was centered around her role as a grandmother and supportive family member rather than carrying out official duties or roles.\n\nSince leaving the White House, Marian Robinson has continued to be an important figure in the Obama family, participating in public events and supporting Michelle Obama's various initiatives.",
